definition: to serve as a vent for
to give often vigorous or emotional expression to
examples: vented her frustration on her coworkers

definition: to relieve by means of a vent
examples: vented himself in a fiery letter to the editor

definition: to relieve oneself by venting something (such as anger)
examples: comes home from work and vents to the kids

definition: an opening for the escape of a gas or liquid or for the relief of pressure: such as
the external opening of the rectum or cloaca : anus
an opening at the breech of a muzzle-loading gun through which fire is touched to the powder
an opportunity or means of escape, passage, or release : outlet
examples: finally gave vent to his pent-up hostility

definition: a slit in a garment, an opening in the lower part of a seam (as of a jacket or skirt)
